cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a new method for imitation learning based on video prediction and deep reinforcement learning, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of deep reinforcement learning suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a likely category. The method involves processing raw video data, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely category. The focus on robotic tasks suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely category. The paper also involves learning from demonstrations, which is a common theme in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing to some extent, as it involves translating context between different environments, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as well.
